{
  "questions": [
    {
      "format": "multipleChoice",
      "context": {
        "description": "Imagine a robot designed to follow written instructions. Before it can act, it looks at the sentence \"Pick up the red cube.\" Instead of seeing 18 individual letters, it identifies four distinct units: 'Pick up' (action), 'the' (article), 'red' (descriptor), and 'cube' (object).",
